      "title": "thatch<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(n.)</div>",
      "html": "<p>古英语单词 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">þæc</i> 指“房屋的屋顶、茅草屋顶、覆盖物”，源自原始日耳曼语词根 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">*thakam</i> （另见于古诺尔斯语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">þak</i>，古弗里斯兰语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">thek</i>，瑞典语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">tak</i>，丹麦语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">tag</i>，中古荷兰语和荷兰语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">dak</i>，古高地日耳曼语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">dah</i>，“覆盖物、盖物”，德语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">Dach</i> “屋顶”），源自原始印欧语根 <a rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of *(s)teg- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/*%28s%29teg-\">*(s)teg-</a> “覆盖”。</p>"
